DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       SSL_CTX_get_verify_mode() returns the verification mode
       currently set in ccttxx.

       SSL_get_verify_mode() returns the verification mode
       currently set in ssssll.

       SSL_CTX_get_verify_depth() returns the verification depth
       limit currently set in ccttxx. If no limit has been
       explicitly set, -1 is returned and the default value will
       be used.

       SSL_get_verify_depth() returns the verification depth
       limit currently set in ssssll. If no limit has been
       explicitly set, -1 is returned and the default value will
       be used.

       SSL_CTX_get_verify_callback() returns a function pointer
       to the verification callback currently set in ccttxx. If no
       callback was explicitly set, the NULL pointer is returned
       and the default callback will be used.

       SSL_get_verify_callback() returns a function pointer to
       the verification callback currently set in ssssll. If no
       callback was explicitly set, the NULL pointer is returned
       and the default callback will be used.

